edna -- an MP3 server

Please see http://www.lyra.org/greg/edna/ for all installation and
usage instructions.

(briefly: edit edna.conf as necessary, then run edna.py)


Placeholder for Greg to move into the HTML docs:
Edna NT service installation:

You also need the most recent Win32 extensions, and have NT 4.0, or
Windows 2000 for this code to work.

    # Installation:
    #   python ednaNTSvc.py -c <path to edna.conf> --startup auto install
    # Removal:
    #   python ednaNTSvc.py remove
    #

Official usage string output by ednaNTSvc.py:
Usage: 'ednaNTSvc.py [options] install|update|remove|start [...]|stop|restart [.
..]|debug [...]'
Options for 'install' and 'update' commands only:
 --username domain\username : The Username the service is to run under
 --password password : The password for the username
 --startup [manual|auto|disabled] : How the service starts, default = manual


Greg Stein, http://www.lyra.org/
February 1999
